(Wang and Liu 2007a,b; Wei and Luo 2008). The system (5) is passive if the following two conditions are satisfied:
F(ulr, uli) and G(ulr, uli) exist, F and the 2m columns of G are smooth vector fields and H(ulr, uli) is a smooth mapping;
∀ t ≥ 0, there is a real value ν satisfying the inequality (6)∫0tθT(τ)η(τ)dτ≥ν, or there exist a constant μ > 0 and a real-valued constant ν which satisfy the inequality (7)∫0tθT(τ)η(τ)dτ+ν≥μ∫0tηT(τ)η(τ)dτ.
